snippet.textDisplay: China has had several pandemics. Bird flu, swine flu, and now Coronavirus. The issue is that the Chinese insist on buying live animals for meat. With 1.4 billion people it’s impossible to monitor all these markets with live animals not to mention all the illegal markets. In most western countries live animals are slaughtered at packing facilities which makes it much easier to monitor. These diseases come from live animals. Unfortunately, even after we get past this one, another one will pop up in a few years. Unless they can change the food supply chain in China, more pandemics will occur. I don’t see that happening.
